22/06/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The leader of the ethnic Hungarian UDMR formation, Marko Bela, announced plans Thursday (June 21st) to step down as deputy prime minister on July 3rd, saying he wants to focus more on his party.
A few weeks ago he indicated he would resign by the end of this month.
(Mediafax, Rompres - 21/06/07)
